'''Claire Elizabeth Hardwick''' (probably better known as '''Charlie Hardwick'''; born 3 November 1960)<ref name="chronicle">[http://www.emmerdale.org/emmerdale/profiles6/val/charliehardwick.htm All about Charlie Hardwick who plays Valerie ("Val") Lambert] ''[[Evening Chronicle]]'', 10 February 2004</ref> is an [[England|English]] [[actress]] well known for her part in [[ITV]]'s ''[[Emmerdale]]'' as [[Val Pollard]].
==Acting career== in addition to her ongoing role in ''Emmerdale'', she also starred in the 2000 comedy film ''[[Purely Belter]]'', and won the best actress award at the [[Festival de TÃ©lÃ©vision de Monte-Carlo|Monte Carlo International Television Festival]] in 1998 for her role in the film ''[[The Scar (film)|The Scar]]'', about a [[County Durham|Durham]] pit community in crisis.<ref name="chronicle"/> She also starred as Sian in ''[[Byker Grove]]''. Played the part of Mrs Castellino in the BBC Radio 4 production "The Little World of Don Camillo", and Our Mam in "My Uncle Freddie", both alongside fellow Emmerdale actor Shaun Prendergast (Greg Dolland). in 2007 Hardwick was an occasional contributor on ''[[Grumpy Old Women]]''.
==Personal life== Hardwick is a fan of [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United Football Club]], holding a [[season ticket]] at [[St. James' Park]], before starting work in ''[[Emmerdale]]'', which meant spending lengthy periods of time away from [[Tyneside]]. She is also a current smoker and prefers roll up cigarettes to ready-rolled cigarettes.
